SUMMARY:Timmy No Brakes LIVE at Pittsburgh Improv
DESCRIPTION:Official TicketsResale Tickets \nAbout the Performer\nTimmy No Brakes is comedy’s most unhinged rising star. A Kill Tony viral menace and Golden Ticket winner\, Timmy has exploded onto the national comedy scene with his off-the-rails energy and deranged confidence that has audiences losing it from the first moment he hits the stage. \nKnown for his high-octane rants\, heterosexual character work\, and pure uncut stupidity delivered with absolute conviction\, Timmy No Brakes is the kind of comedian you have to see live to truly believe. His Kill Tony appearances have racked up millions of views online\, turning him into one of the most talked-about new voices in stand-up comedy. \nIf you’re looking for a comedy show that’s completely unpredictable\, wildly funny\, and unlike anything you’ve seen before\, Timmy No Brakes is your guy. Buckle up — this show is going to be a ride. \nEvent Details\nDate: Friday\, July 3\, 2026 \nTime: 7:00 PM (Doors open at 5:30 PM) \nVenue: Pittsburgh Improv\, 166 E. Bridge St\, Homestead\, PA 15120 \nAge Restriction: Ages 21 and up \nAdditional Shows: A late show is also available at 9:30 PM on Friday\, July 3\, and two shows on Saturday\, July 4 at 6:30 PM and 9:00 PM. \nAbout the Venue\nThe Pittsburgh Improv is located at 166 E. Bridge Street in Homestead\, PA — just minutes from downtown Pittsburgh. As part of the nationally recognized Improv Comedy Club chain\, the Pittsburgh Improv is one of the premier comedy venues in the region. \nThe club features a full-service restaurant and bar\, making it a perfect destination for a complete night out. The intimate showroom seats approximately 300 guests\, ensuring every seat has a great sightline to the stage. The venue’s lively atmosphere is ideal for the kind of high-energy comedy that Timmy No Brakes delivers. \nParking is available nearby\, and the venue is easily accessible from major highways. Note that this show falls on the July 4th holiday weekend\, so plan ahead for traffic and parking. The Pittsburgh Improv is known for bringing top national touring comedians to the Pittsburgh area. \nWhat to Expect\nTimmy No Brakes delivers a stand-up performance that is completely unhinged\, wildly energetic\, and absolutely hilarious. This is a solo stand-up show — expect 60–75 minutes of non-stop\, unpredictable comedy that will have you in tears. \nHis shows are known for being spontaneous and electric. Timmy’s comedy blends absurdist character work with rapid-fire observations and crowd interaction. No two shows are the same\, and Pittsburgh audiences are in for a treat on the July 4th holiday weekend. \nPlease note: This is an ages 21 and up event. Valid ID is required at the door. Third-party tickets will not be honored — purchase only from authorized sellers. \nTicket Information\nPrice Range: $25 – $69 (plus fees) \nTickets are available through official channels and resale marketplaces. This show falls on the July 4th holiday weekend\, so tickets are expected to sell quickly. Purchase early to secure your spot! \nOfficial TicketsResale Tickets \nThis post contains affiliate links. We may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.
URL:https://comedycalendar.com/event/timmy-no-brakes-live-at-pittsburgh-improv/
LOCATION:Pittsburgh Improv\, 166 E. Bridge St\, Homestead\, Pennsylvania\, 15120\, United States
