SUMMARY:50 First Jokes About America LIVE at Punch Line Philly
DESCRIPTION:This post contains affiliate links. We earn a commission if you purchase tickets through our links at no extra cost to you. \nOfficial Tickets\nResale Tickets \n50 First Jokes About America LIVE at Punch Line Philly\nGet ready for a hilarious patriotic comedy extravaganza as 50 First Jokes About America takes the stage at Punch Line Philly in Philadelphia\, PA on July 3\, 2026 — just in time for Independence Day weekend! This all-star comedy showcase celebrates America through the lens of stand-up comedy\, featuring a rotating lineup of top comedians delivering their best material about life in the USA. \nEvent Details\nDate: Friday\, July 3\, 2026\nTime: 7:00 PM EDT\nVenue: Punch Line Philly\nAddress: 33 E. Laurel Street\, Philadelphia\, PA 19123\nAge Requirement: 21+ (18+ with parent or legal guardian over 30)\nDrink Minimum: 2-beverage minimum per person \nAbout 50 First Jokes About America\n50 First Jokes About America is a special comedy showcase celebrating the nation’s birthday weekend with 50 hilarious jokes about American life\, culture\, and everything in between. Featuring some of the best comedians in the country\, this show is the perfect way to kick off your Fourth of July celebrations with laughter. Past editions have featured comedians who have appeared on Comedy Central\, late-night talk shows\, and major streaming platforms. \nWhat to Expect\n\nA high-energy patriotic comedy showcase perfect for Independence Day weekend\nMultiple comedians delivering their best material about American life\nAn intimate club setting at one of Philadelphia’s premier comedy venues\nFull bar service with cocktails\, beer\, and wine available\nA fun\, festive atmosphere to celebrate the holiday weekend\nDoors open 1 hour before showtime — arrive early for the best seats\n\nVenue Information\nPunch Line Philly is Philadelphia’s premier stand-up comedy club\, located at 33 E. Laurel Street in the heart of the city. The intimate showroom offers excellent sightlines from every seat\, and the Callback Bar opens 1 hour before showtime for pre-show drinks and mingling. Parking lots are available behind the venue at 49 Richmond Street and 1025 N. Front Street. \nTicket Information\nTickets for 50 First Jokes About America at Punch Line Philly are available now. Resale tickets start at $44. There is an 8-ticket limit per person. Tickets are non-refundable unless the event is cancelled or postponed. \nOfficial Tickets\nResale Tickets \nThis post contains affiliate links. We earn a commission if you purchase tickets through our links at no extra cost to you. \nAll sales are final. Show times subject to change. Valid photo ID may be required for entry.
URL:https://comedycalendar.com/event/fifty-first-jokes-about-america-live-at-punch-line-philly/
LOCATION:Punch Line Philly\, 33 E. Laurel Street\, Philadelphia\, PA\, 19123\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://comedycalendar.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/65a5db7c-e977-4368-bed6-5246ab6ac60c_SOURCE-VWy9Ew.png
GEO:39.9652742;-75.1351879
