SUMMARY:Benji Brown LIVE at Arlington Improv (Friday Late Show)
DESCRIPTION:Official TicketsResale Tickets \nThis post contains affiliate links. We may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. \nAbout the Performer\nBenji Brown is an urban comedian setting a new standard in comedy. He toured with Martin Lawrence’s 2018 LIT AF Tour and is now the host of Martin Lawrence’s “Yall Know What It Is Tour.” His viral character KiKi has garnered over 3 million views\, cementing him as one of the next major urban comedic household names. \nEvent Details\nDate: Friday\, July 3\, 2026 \nTime: 9:45 PM (Late Show) \nVenue: Arlington Improv\, 309 Curtis Mathes Way #147\, Arlington\, TX 76018 \nAge Restriction: 18+ \nPrice Range: $20 to $60 per person \nAbout the Venue\nArlington Improv is located in the Highlands Shopping Center in Arlington\, TX\, across from Torchy’s Tacos. It is an intimate comedy club featuring a full bar and restaurant where guests enjoy world-renowned and local comics in a lively\, up-close setting. The venue also hosts Black Dog Pizza Arcade with 30+ local craft beers. \nWhat to Expect\nBenji Brown closes out Friday night at Arlington Improv with a full late-show headlining set. Expect his signature urban humor\, character work\, and high-energy delivery — the perfect late-night way to kick off your 4th of July weekend. \nThis is an 18+ event. Food and beverage service ends approximately 45 minutes into the show. All sales are final. \nTicket Information\nTickets range from $20 to $60 per person. Purchase official tickets or find resale options below. \nOfficial TicketsResale Tickets
URL:https://comedycalendar.com/event/benji-brown-live-at-arlington-improv-friday-late/
